The paper discusses the challenge of human-computer interaction with intelligent systems and the need for transparency, scrutability, intelligibility, interpretability, and explainability. These topics are all related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for users to have knowledge outcomes, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper provides a conceptual framework for understanding user mindsets and involvement, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
